### CSS (styles.css)
```css
body {
    background-color: #0a0a0a;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

.container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 20px;
    margin: auto;
    max-width: 1000px;
    color: white;
}

.chatTo achieve a similar design for this image using web development, you'd primarily use HTML, CSS, and possibly some JavaScript for interactions or animations.

Here's a basic example using HTML and CSS to create chat bubbles, notifications, and emoji indicators with a neon outline effect similar to the style you shared:

### HTML
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Chat Design</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="chat">
            <div class="bubble neon-green"><span class="icon user"></span></div>
            <div class="bubble neon-blue"><span>Message bubble</span></div>
            <div class="bubble neon-orange"><span>Typing...</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="notifications">
            <div class="emoji neon-pink">ðŸ˜„<span class="count">6</span></div>
            <div class="message-alert neon-red"><span class="icon"></span><span class="count">1</span></div>
            <div class="status neon-green"><span class="checkmark">âœ”âœ”</span></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS (styles.css)
```css
body {
    background-color: #0a0a0a;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

.container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 20px;
    margin: auto;
    max-width: 1000px;
    color: white;
}

.chat
